WEBVTT

00:04.000 --> 00:07.148
<i>♪ We are the Crystal Gems ♪</i>

00:07.249 --> 00:09.770
<i>♪ we'll always save the day ♪</i>

00:09.831 --> 00:11.903
<i>♪ and if you think we can't ♪</i>

00:11.905 --> 00:14.772
<i>♪ we'll always find a way ♪</i>

00:14.774 --> 00:18.676
<i>- # that's why the people #
- # of this world #</i>

00:18.678 --> 00:21.045
<i>- # believe in... #
- # Garnet #</i>

00:21.047 --> 00:23.848
<i>- # Amethyst #
- # and Pearl #</i>

00:23.850 --> 00:25.517
<i>♪ And Steven! ♪</i>

00:25.681 --> 00:27.374
1x35
<b> "Lion 3: Straight to Video" </b>

00:27.378 --> 00:29.299
<i><font color=#ca> ~ Fora Temer ~ </font></i>

00:31.013 --> 00:34.278
<i>Hmmm...</i>

00:35.362 --> 00:40.533
Hmmm...
hmmmm-hmmm...

00:40.618 --> 00:43.453
- You can do it, Steven.
- Thanks Sadie.

00:43.504 --> 00:46.089
It's just...
I could get a donut, which

00:46.173 --> 00:48.625
would be tasty.
But I always get donuts.

00:48.676 --> 00:52.262
Shouldn't I be living life to
the fullest and trying new things?

00:52.263 --> 00:55.848
So tonight, maybe I'm
thinking... spicy pretzels?

00:55.933 --> 00:57.884
Why don't you ask your little friend?

01:03.140 --> 01:05.224
Ugh, lion those are gross.

01:05.309 --> 01:08.061
- No offense.
- You kids better hurry it up.

01:08.145 --> 01:10.130
Lars and I are closing up...

01:18.289 --> 01:22.125
I'm closing up for the day.

01:22.159 --> 01:25.461
Hey, Sadie!
There's a snack named after you?

01:25.546 --> 01:28.798
Nah, those are all lunches
my mom packed for me.

01:28.832 --> 01:32.669
- Aww, that's so nice!
- Eh... actually, it's pretty

01:32.753 --> 01:35.421
embarrassing. She's
been doing it for years.

01:35.506 --> 01:37.390
I mean, I know how to feed myself!

01:37.474 --> 01:40.560
They just make me feel
like a kid, you know?

01:40.678 --> 01:42.679
- Can I try one?
- Sure.

01:42.763 --> 01:44.935
But choose wisely.
Some of those have been

01:44.999 --> 01:46.582
in there for a few months.

01:46.817 --> 01:49.652
Alrighty, let's
see what we got here.

01:49.687 --> 01:52.739
Look like a classic PBJ
sandwich cut into triangles!

01:52.823 --> 01:56.159
Very nice! It's the only
shape a sandwich should be.

01:56.160 --> 01:59.495
<i>Mama Sadie, this lunch is a win!
And for dessert we have...</i>

01:59.530 --> 02:01.614
<i>Whoa! Look at this!</i>

02:01.699 --> 02:04.701
Lion! Lion look!
It's a cookie shaped like a star!

02:06.787 --> 02:09.339
I guess you could say this cookie is...

02:09.372 --> 02:11.374
out of this world. Eh?

02:16.847 --> 02:19.716
I wonder what kind of lunch
my mom would've made me?

02:19.800 --> 02:24.220
Maybe actual space cookies!

02:24.305 --> 02:29.726
I just wish...
I knew a little more about her.

02:33.447 --> 02:36.099
Blink if this means you love me!

02:38.285 --> 02:39.902
He loves me!

02:40.738 --> 02:42.872
All done!
I made sure to make it extra

02:42.906 --> 02:44.991
skooshy, just the way you like it!

02:45.075 --> 02:47.577
Wha... hey!

02:47.661 --> 02:49.962
Hey, get out of there!

02:50.047 --> 02:53.249
Lion, this is the Steven
bed not the lion bed!

02:53.334 --> 02:54.834
Come on!

02:54.918 --> 02:59.505
Whoa!
Hey! That's mine too!

02:59.590 --> 03:02.346
And Sir Bearington.

03:05.995 --> 03:09.265
<i>'Night lion!</i>

03:09.316 --> 03:15.502
Love you...
in the morning.

03:20.611 --> 03:24.280
<i>Whoa...
What is this place?</i>

03:24.415 --> 03:26.916
<i>I can't breathe!</i>

03:27.350 --> 03:30.787
<i>Steven!
Steven! Steven! Steven!</i>

03:30.838 --> 03:32.955
Steven! Oh my gosh!
Oh my gosh!

03:33.006 --> 03:35.017
Hang on! I got you!

03:35.106 --> 03:38.422
Ugh, lion! Let him go!

03:40.547 --> 03:44.434
- What happened?
- Steven, are you all right?

03:44.468 --> 03:47.387
Why was lion sleeping on top of you?

03:47.471 --> 03:50.536
I don't know.
He's being a little clingy today.

03:50.557 --> 03:53.393
But that's cause I'm his
favorite! Oh!

03:53.477 --> 03:54.560
<i>See? Wait...</i>

03:54.645 --> 03:57.280
Why are you here, Pearl?

03:57.364 --> 03:59.315
Me?
Nothing. I was just uh...

03:59.400 --> 04:01.401
well, you know how I always say...

04:01.485 --> 04:04.987
um, I just uh...
I like to watch you sleep

04:05.072 --> 04:08.771
sometimes. And by
sometimes I mean often.

04:09.176 --> 04:12.204
Okeydokey, it's time
for everyone to leave Steven alone.

04:12.312 --> 04:16.245
I'm a growing boy
and I needs my rest.

04:19.269 --> 04:22.896
Lion, that means you too.

04:24.657 --> 04:27.443
Rah! Rah! Rah! Rah! Rah!

